  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Matter of weeks.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It-- things happened very quickly, as history divulges.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On September 1, 1939, the Germans attacked Poland, and we were at war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the conversations that I'm recalling must have occurred within a week of that or two weeks at the most of that occurrence.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] From that point forward, I knew, of course, that war was not quite what I thought it was because of the airplanes and the bombing and the ack ack and the, the, the machine gun fire that, that I would hear.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But by then we had already moved, and that's a different part of the story.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My, my life changed considerably the week before war began because my father, in preparation of the possibility of bombing, decided that we should move to his building-- his being what he had inherited from his parents-- which is a brick building near the outskirts of Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And where we lived was in the center of Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that his reasoning was that there was less chance of bombing in the outskirts of Bialystok in the first place.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the second place being that it was a brick building, two-story affair, it would be stronger and could withstand perhaps the shelling or whatever.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so he took it upon himself to move the family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we, we joined my father's mother-- my grandmother-- and Bobble, the aunt that lived there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father, mother, and I and my maternal grandmother all moved into the same premises-- the building on [POLISH] near the outskirts of Bialystok.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we did that prior to the war breaking out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That changed my life forever and things were never, from then on again, the same because events just carried away.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
